Script runs clean. Output is 1,455 characters on a healthy repo — well within the 4,000 target with plenty of headroom for failures to expand into.

**What it covers:**

| Section | Signal |
|---|---|
| Git Status | `git status --short` — shows dirty working tree |
| Recent Commits | last 10 oneline |
| Sprint | active increment name + description from `prd/manifest.json` |
| Helm Lint | Pass/Fail counts across all 33 charts; details only on failure |
| Contract Validator (G7) | Tests valid.yaml passes + all invalid-*.yaml reject |
| Autarky (G6) | Grep for external registry refs in chart templates |
| Shellcheck | Silent on clean; error count + first 15 lines on failure |
| State Docs (G2) | Presence check for `docs/state/agent.md` + `architecture.md` |
| CI | Lists `.github/workflows/*.yml` |

Happy path stays at ~1,500 chars. Failure paths expand per section, capped with `head` to prevent runaway output.
